lth </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> said samples taken over the weekend of drinking water in <LOCATION> Broomfield </LOCATION> and other communities were not contaminated by any of 59 organic substances typically analyzed in checking drinking water. However, the state still was testing for 13 other chemicals cited by federal investigators in their probe of Rocky Flats. Results were expected later in the week, department assistant director <PERSON> Tom </PERSON> <PERSON> Looby </PERSON> said. `` We are confident that these initial tests indicate that the likelihood of any of the 13 chemicals being found in these drinking water supplies is very, very small,'' <PERSON> Looby </PERSON> said.
