hip, when at least 8,961 people were arrested, never seen again and presumed executed. Human rights groups claim the death toll is much higher. The armed forces claims it used unconventional tactics to fight an unconventional enemy and save <LOCATION> Argentina </LOCATION>'s democracy. The military returned to the barracks after presiding over an economic collapse, losing the 1982 Falklands War to <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION> and encountering worldwide condemnation over its human rights policies.
