 Framed against majestic, snow-streaked mountains, President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> rallied Americans on Tuesday to support his plan for combatting air pollution, saying, `` Nature needs our help.'' One day after unveiling a proposal for cleaning up acid-rain pollutants, smog and toxic chemicals from the air, <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> declared, `` Environmental gridlock must end.'' Despite disputes among energy, mining, chemical and environmental groups about what to do, <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> said, `` There's one thing everyone agrees on. We need action. And we need it now.'' He said competing interests in <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> have `` jammed the avenue to action'' for more than a decade.
